			<use xlink:href="/uswds/img/usa-icons/sprite.svg#share"></use>
		</svg>
	</a>

	<div class="link-content display-none"><input class="clipboard-input-field tooltip" aria-label="Link to content" data-tippy-content="Click to copy to clipboard" type="text" value="https://nca2023.globalchange.gov/chapter/12#table-12-1" readonly/></div>
</div>

        <div class="table-header">
            <hr class="secondary-blue-line-table">
            <div class="table-title">Table 12.1. Examples of Mitigation and Adaptation Options in Cities and Built Environments</div>
        </div>
        
            <div class="table-caption">These examples of mitigation and adaptation options are drawn from published sources or from other NCA5 chapters. Examples are illustrative and do not represent a comprehensive list. A longer discussion of potential greenhouse gas emissions reductions by mitigation actions can be found in Chapter <a target="_blank" href="/chapter/32">32</a> (see Figure <a target="_blank" href="/chapter/32#fig-32-22">32.22</a>). Option categories are adapted from Carmin et al. 2015; IPCC 2022, 2022; and Dodman et al. 2022.<sup><a href="#fn:122" rel="footnote" onclick="return false;">122</a></sup><sup class="cm">,</sup><sup><a href="#fn:123" rel="footnote" onclick="return false;">123</a></sup><sup class="cm">,</sup><sup><a href="#fn:124" rel="footnote" onclick="return false;">124</a></sup><sup class="cm">,</sup><sup><a href="#fn:125" rel="footnote" onclick="return false;">125</a></sup></div><table class="tsu-table">
